find_nomic_rule

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
find_nomic_rule -  This method searches through for the specified rule.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
class nomic_rule find_nomic_rule(string area,
string creator,
string text)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^area%^RESET%^ - the area the rule is in
%^BOLD%^creator%^RESET%^ - the creator of the rule
%^BOLD%^text%^RESET%^ - the text of the rule
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the rule if it is found, 0 if not
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/obj/handlers/inherit/nomic_rules.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method searches through for the specified rule.  This stops the
same rule being added more than once by some error in the code.
.EP

